Rift Valley fever in Saudi Arabia - Update as of 8 Oct 2000
-----------------------------------------------------------
As of 8 October, the Ministry of Health of Saudi Arabia has reported 291
suspected cases of Rift Valley fever, including 64 deaths. The World Health
Organization (WHO) in conjunction with its international partners from the
WHO Collaborating Centers at the US Centers for Disease Control and
Prevention in the United States of America and the National Institute of
Virology in South Africa, has been providing the Saudi government with
advice and assistance with field investigation and implementation of
control measures to contain the spread of the disease. Updates detailing
events and measures taken since the start of the outbreak can be found on
the Saudi Arabia Information Resource web site at
<http://www.saudinf.com/main/yy1.htm>.
